(337, 62, '_form', '<div class=\"intro\"> \n<p>An objectives analysis provides the starting point for determining what solutions are possible. You should perform an objectives analysis for each of the problems identified in the problem analysis.</p>\n<p><i>Below is a form you can use to perform an objectives analysis. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</i></p>\n<b>Objectives tree</b>\n<p>An objectives tree is similar to a problem tree, except that the objectives tree illustrates objectives (intentions) rather than problems.</p>\n<p>If a problem tree has been created, you can easily turn it into an objectives tree by converting the causes at the root of the problem tree into objective statements. Enter.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The positive <b>objective statements</b> at the bottom of the tree, and\n</li>\n<li>The <b>outcomes</b> that will result when the objectives are met at the top\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n<button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\n</div>'),
