(1529, 165, '_form', '<div class=\"intro\"> \n<h5><b>Facilitate rehabilitation activities</b></h5>\n<p>CBR can facilitate home and community-based therapy services and provide assistance to people with a wide range of impairments, enabling them to maintain and maximize their function within their home and community. The following form lists a number of important areas where CBR can provide support.</p>\n<p><em>Complete this form to identify areas where you believe your organization would be able to most effectively provide support. Select <b>Save</b> when you are finished.</em></p>\n<p>CBR can facilitate rehabilitation activities in a number of different areas, some of the most important of which are listed below.</p>\n<p><b>Provide early intervention activities for child development</b></p>\n<p>Every child goes through a learning process enabling him/her to master important skills for life. The major areas of child development include:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Physical development</li>\n<li>Speech and language development</li>\n<li>Cognitive development, and</li>\n<li>Social and emotional development</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Delays in development occur when a child is unable to reach the important milestones suitable for his or her age group. Through early intervention, children at risk of, or with, developmental delay are identified as early as possible and provided with focused rehabilitation interventions to prevent or reduce this delay.</p>\n<p>The presence of a disability, such as cerebral palsy, blindness or deafness can result in developmental delay and restrict a child’s ability to participate in regular activities such as playing with other children and going to school.</p>\n<p>To facilitate the provision of early intervention activities for children who need them, CBR personnel can:</p>\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[checkbox checkbox-301 id:checkbox class:cf-165-1 \"Provide early intervention activities (usually home-based) to encourage simple and enjoyable learning opportunities for development\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\"><b>Example</b>: Simple stimulation activities for children with sensory impairments</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[checkbox checkbox-301 id:checkbox class:cf-165-1 \"Encourage parents to meet together to share ideas and experiences\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[checkbox checkbox-301 id:checkbox class:cf-165-1 \"Work with parents to facilitate playgroups, so their children:\"]\n<ul>\n<li>Learn to play with other children</li>\n<li>Learn new skills, and</li>\n<li>Improve in all areas of development</li>\n</ul></div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><b>Encourage functional independence</b></p>\n<p>Functional interventions aim to improve an individual’s level of independence in daily living skills, such as mobility, communication, bathing, toileting, dressing, eating, drinking, cooking and housework. Interventions are dependent on a person’s age, gender and local environment and will change over time as he or she makes a transition from one life stage to another.</p>\n<p>To support functional interventions, CBR personnel can provide:</p>\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[checkbox checkbox-301 id:checkbox class:cf-165-5 \"Training for people with disabilities and their families about the different ways to carry out activities\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[checkbox checkbox-301 id:checkbox class:cf-165-5 \"Education for families on how to best assist people with disabilities in functional activities to maximize their independence\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">&nbsp</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[checkbox checkbox-301 id:checkbox class:cf-165-5 \"Training in the use of assistive devices to make activities easier\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\"><b>Examples</b>: Walking and mobility devices</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[checkbox checkbox-301 id:checkbox class:cf-165-5 \"Education and instruction on specific techniques used to address impairments which impact a person’s ability to carry out activities\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\"><b>Examples:</b> Strengthening, stretching and fitness programmes may provide benefits for:<ul><li>Muscle weakness</li>\n<li>Poor balance</li>\n<li>Muscle tightness</li>\n</ul></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><b>Facilitate environmental modifications</b></p>\n<p>Environmental modifications may be necessary to improve the functional independence of a person with a disability. CBR personnel may facilitate environmental modifications at:</p>\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2 vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-301 id:checkbox class:cf-165-5 \"An individual level in the home\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\"><b>Examples:</b><ul><li>Ramps for wheelchair access</li>\n<li>Handrails near steps</li>\n<li>Toilet adaptations</li>\n<li>Widening doorways</li>\n</ul></div>\n</div>\n\n\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\">[checkbox checkbox-301 id:checkbox class:cf-165-5 \"The community level\"]</div>\n<div class=\"rTableCell p-2\"><b>Examples:</b>Modifications to:<ul><li>School</li>\n<li>Public buildings</li>\n<li>Work places</li>\n</ul></div></div></div></div>'),
