(84, 1, '2019-05-06 05:27:19', '2019-05-06 05:27:19', '<div class=\"intro\"> \r\n<h3>Carry out planned activities</h3>\r\n<p>CBR programme managers need to be very familiar with their organization’s work plans and be able to make the necessary preparations to ensure that all the activities are carried out as planned.\r\n</p>\r\n<p><i>The checklist below identifies general activities that nearly every CBR programme will undertake. Select Save when you are finished.</i></p>\r\n<p>General activities that are undertaken by nearly every CBR programme include:</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTable\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"\r\n <b>Awareness-raising </b> activities directed at stakeholders\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> The goals of awareness-raising are to<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Provide information and knowledge about disability</li>\r\n<li>Generate attitudinal and behaviour change</li>\r\n<li>Generate support for the CBR strategy and programmes</li>\r\n<li>Encourage stakeholder involvement and participation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"<b>Coordinating and networking</b> with stakeholders\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> The goals are to:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Build good relationships and partnerships</li>\r\n<li>Share knowledge and resources</li>\r\n<li>Reduce duplication of effort</li>\r\n<li>Mobilize community resources</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"<b>Mainstreaming</b> activities\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b> The goal is to ensure that people with disabilities are able to fully participate and are supported in each development sector.<br>\r\n<p>Mainstreaming activities are accompanied by specific measures (e.g. reasonable accommodation to ensure access to equal opportunities).\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"<b>Providing services</b>\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>Each programme will provide a different range of services, which may include:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Identification of people with disabilities</li>\r\n<li>Referrals to mainstream/specialized services</li>\r\n<li>Reduce duplication of effort</li>\r\n<li>Providing basic rehabilitation</li>\r\n<li>Providing simple assistive devices</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"<b>Advocacy </b> activities\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Note:</b>Many different types of advocacy activities can be used to ensure that equal opportunities and rights for people with disabilities are achieved in every aspect of community life. Among the tools that can be used to increase social accountability are:<br>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Social audits</li>\r\n<li>Community score cards</li>\r\n<li>Citizen report cards</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"rTableRow style=\"width: 100%;\">\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\">[checkbox checkbox-263 id:checkbox111 class:check13 \"<b>Capacity building</b> activities (to ensure that stakeholders possess the knowledge and skills required to carry out their roles and responsibilities)\"]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"rTableCell vertical\"><p><b>Existing training programmes for stakeholders:</b></p><br>[text text-286 id:text01 class:textbox]<br><br>[text text-286 id:text02 class:textbox]<br><br>[text text-286 id:text02 class:textbox]<br>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<br><button type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">Save</button>\r\n      <button type=\"reset\" value=\"Reset\">Print</button>\r\n</div>\n1\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\nbomoxuxul@parcel4.net\nFrom: [your-name] <[your-email]>\r\nSubject: [your-subject]\r\n\r\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\n\n\n\n\n\nINCLUDE: \"[your-subject]\"\nINCLUDE: <wordpress@include.xyz>\n[your-email]\nMessage Body:\r\n[your-message]\r\n\r\n-- \r\nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on INCLUDE: (http://include.xyz)\nReply-To: bomoxuxul@parcel4.net\n\n\n\nThank you for your message. It has been sent.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nOne or more fields have an error. Please check and try again.\nThere was an error trying to send your message. Please try again later.\nYou must accept the terms and conditions before sending your message.\nThe field is required.\nThe field is too long.\nThe field is too short.\nThe date format is incorrect.\nThe date is before the earliest one allowed.\nThe date is after the latest one allowed.\nThere was an unknown error uploading the file.\nYou are not allowed to upload files of this type.\nThe file is too big.\nThere was an error uploading the file.\nThe number format is invalid.\nThe number is smaller than the minimum allowed.\nThe number is larger than the maximum allowed.\nThe answer to the quiz is incorrect.\nYour entered code is incorrect.\nThe e-mail address entered is invalid.\nThe URL is invalid.\nThe telephone number is invalid.', 'Carry out planned activities', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'untitled-7', '', '', '2019-05-06 07